WEBVTT

00:03.503 --> 00:05.971
[ SIRENS WAILING IN DISTANCE ]

00:05.973 --> 00:08.040
[ INDISTINCT TALKING ]

00:10.844 --> 00:13.412
[ TALKING CONTINUES, MUFFLED ]

00:22.489 --> 00:24.289
[ SPLASH ]

00:43.710 --> 00:45.411
Man: SHE'S UP! SHE'S UP!

00:45.413 --> 00:46.645
GOT HER OVER HERE!

00:46.647 --> 00:48.480
GO, GO, GO, GO!

00:48.482 --> 00:50.516
BRING HER IN.

00:59.692 --> 01:00.859
[ SIREN WAILING ]

01:13.573 --> 01:15.174
WHY'S THE FIRE DEPARTMENT
HERE?

01:15.176 --> 01:16.842
DIVERS. DEAD WIFE
AT THE BOTTOM OF THE POOL.

01:16.844 --> 01:18.510
YEAH, YEAH.
I'M HOLDING.

01:18.512 --> 01:20.446
THE BETTER QUESTION IS,
WHAT ARE <i>YOU</i> DOING HERE?

01:20.448 --> 01:22.614
I THOUGHT YOU WERE GOING
TO ROBINSON'S RETIREMENT
DINNER TONIGHT.

01:22.616 --> 01:24.249
YEAH,
WES ROBINSON'S GONE.

01:24.251 --> 01:27.419
THAT MAKES ME THE LAST MEMBER
OF MY ACADEMY CLASS

01:27.421 --> 01:28.854
STILL ON THE JOB.

01:28.856 --> 01:31.457
SO YOU COLLECTED!
HOW MUCH WAS IN THE TROPHY?

01:31.459 --> 01:32.891
MAYBE $4,000.

01:32.893 --> 01:36.195
THAT'S GREAT! THAT'S YOUR REWARD
FOR MAKING HISTORY.

01:36.197 --> 01:37.863
YEAH.
AND RELIVING IT.

01:37.865 --> 01:40.466
OVER AND OVER.

01:44.804 --> 01:47.239
LET ME GUESS.

01:47.241 --> 01:50.309
THE VICTIM WAS MARRIED,
SO HER HUSBAND CALLED IT IN.

01:50.311 --> 01:51.443
YOU MUST BE PSYCHIC.

01:51.445 --> 01:52.578
YEAH.

01:52.580 --> 01:54.613
LIEUTENANT FLYNN,
MAJOR CRIMES.

01:54.615 --> 01:56.482
RIGHT.
I NEED A T.O.D.

01:56.484 --> 01:58.217
WHERE ARE YOU PEOPLE?

01:58.219 --> 02:00.252
SO, WHAT SORT OF SORRY EXCUSE
DID THIS HUSBAND HAVE?

02:00.254 --> 02:01.553
WELL,
HE CAME HOME FROM WORK

02:01.555 --> 02:03.622
TO FIND HIS WIFE
AT THE BOTTOM OF THE POOL.

02:03.624 --> 02:07.259
I SEE LOTS OF BLOOD,
SO NO DROWNING, I GUESS.

02:07.261 --> 02:08.861
NO -- YES.
STABBED TO DEATH.

02:08.863 --> 02:10.996
FOUND A KNIFE
AT THE BOTTOM OF THE POOL.

02:10.998 --> 02:12.331
LOOKS RIGHT.

02:12.333 --> 02:13.465
YEAH, WELL,
WHERE'S THE HUSBAND?

02:13.467 --> 02:16.335
HE'S OVER THERE, SIR.

02:16.337 --> 02:18.871
SYKES, TELL ME, UH...

02:18.873 --> 02:21.907
WAS THE "ALARM NOT SET,"
OR DID HE FAKE A BREAK-IN?

02:21.909 --> 02:23.475
EXCELLENT QUESTION,
SIR.

02:23.477 --> 02:25.010
NO SIGN
OF FORCED ENTRY.

02:25.012 --> 02:26.912
MOTION DETECTORS
INSIDE THE HOUSE,

02:26.914 --> 02:29.448
PERIMETER ALARM CONTROLLED
VIA KEYPAD OUTSIDE.

02:29.450 --> 02:31.416
THE TOP OF HIS BACKYARD WALLS
INCLUDE PRESSURE SENSORS

02:31.418 --> 02:33.252
FOR ANYTHING
OVER 30 POUNDS.

02:33.254 --> 02:35.454
YEAH, JUST LIKE IN HIS THIRD
MOVIE ABOUT THAT BURGLAR GUY.

02:36.422 --> 02:39.424
SET IN A RUSSIAN PRISON?
CALLED "CAT IN THE BAG"?

02:39.426 --> 02:41.293
OUR VICTIM'S HUSBAND
IS MARTIN ELLIOT.

02:41.295 --> 02:42.728
HE'S A BIG-TIME
FILM DIRECTOR.

02:42.730 --> 02:43.962
BUT YOU'RE RIGHT --

02:43.964 --> 02:45.797
MR. ELLIOT SAYS
THE ALARM WAS OFF

02:45.799 --> 02:46.965
WHEN HE GOT HERE.

02:46.967 --> 02:48.333
WELL, IF HE FOUND HIS WIFE
IN THE POOL,

02:48.335 --> 02:49.635
SHOULDN'T HE BE WET?

02:49.637 --> 02:51.370
Sanchez: WELL,
HE DIDN'T TRY TO RESCUE HER.

02:51.372 --> 02:53.005
HE JUST CALLED 911.
UH-HUH.

02:53.007 --> 02:55.340
BUZZ, IN CASE
WE DON'T GET A CHANCE

02:55.342 --> 02:58.377
TO TALK TO MR. ELLIOT AGAIN,
UH, LET'S FILM HIM HERE NOW.

02:58.379 --> 02:59.745
YES, SIR.

02:59.747 --> 03:03.115
AND, SYKES, CAREFULLY REMIND HIM
OF HIS RIGHTS.

03:07.954 --> 03:11.356
OKAY. NEVER-ENDING
BUDGET CRISIS.

03:11.358 --> 03:13.659
THE MORGUE CAN'T GET ANYBODY
OUT HERE UNTIL 5:00 A.M.

03:13.661 --> 03:14.760
IT'S OKAY.

03:16.496 --> 03:18.363
SHE HAS
NO PLACE ELSE TO BE.

03:21.968 --> 03:23.936
OF COURSE
I'M AWARE OF MY RIGHTS.

03:23.938 --> 03:25.871
I GOT MY START
CREATING THE NUMBER-ONE

03:25.873 --> 03:27.973
COP REALITY SERIES
OF ALL TIME,

03:27.975 --> 03:29.708
"YOU HAVE THE RIGHT
TO REMAIN SILENT."

03:29.710 --> 03:31.577
DO YOU REALLY NEED ME
TO GO THROUGH THIS STORY

03:31.579 --> 03:32.911
FOR A THIRD TIME?

03:32.913 --> 03:35.047
WHAT YOU SAY NOW
WILL GO A LONG WAY

03:35.049 --> 03:37.049
TO HELPING US
FIND THE KILLER.

03:38.885 --> 03:39.952
FINE.

03:41.321 --> 03:42.754
I CAME HOME FROM WORK
TO --
EHT-EHT.

03:45.558 --> 03:47.993
I CAME HOME FROM WORK
11:00 THIS EVENING.

03:47.995 --> 03:49.995
I THOUGHT THAT GRETCHEN
HAD GONE TO BED,

03:49.997 --> 03:52.798
SO I WENT UPSTAIRS,
AND I LOOKED OUT THE WINDOW.

03:52.800 --> 03:56.802
THEN I SAW BLOOD IN THE WATER,
AND I CALLED 911.

03:58.605 --> 04:00.505
<i>HOW LONG</i>
<i>IS THIS GONNA TAKE, MAN?</i>

04:00.507 --> 04:03.909
<i>I GOT -- MY PHONE IS INSIDE.</i>
<i>I GOT TO GET TO MY PHONE.</i>

04:03.911 --> 04:05.544
<i>ARE WE DONE?</i>

04:05.546 --> 04:07.379
THANK YOU, BUZZ.

04:07.381 --> 04:09.881
AND REMIND LIEUTENANT TAO
ABOUT THE SPECIAL PRESS RELEASE

04:09.883 --> 04:11.516
I ASKED HIM
TO MAKE UP FOR ME.

04:11.518 --> 04:12.918
WILL DO.

04:12.920 --> 04:14.086
OKAY.

04:14.088 --> 04:15.687
FIRST, THE BODY
WAS AT THE BOTTOM

04:15.689 --> 04:17.389
OF A HEATED POOL
FOR A WHILE,

04:17.391 --> 04:18.957
THEN LEFT OUT IN THE NIGHT AIR
TILL EARLY THIS MORNING,

04:18.959 --> 04:20.626
SO I HAVE TO PUT
THE TIME OF DEATH

04:20.628 --> 04:22.928
AS BETWEEN
7:00 AND 11:00 P.M.

04:22.930 --> 04:24.930
BUT THAT'S NOT
THE WORST OF IT.

04:24.932 --> 04:27.032
WHAT COULD BE WORSE
THAN A FOUR-HOUR WINDOW

04:27.034 --> 04:28.500
FOR TIME OF DEATH?

04:28.502 --> 04:30.535
THE VICTIM WAS...
THREE MONTHS PREGNANT.

04:30.537 --> 04:33.905
SO...
<i>DOUBLE</i> HOMICIDE.

04:33.907 --> 04:37.042
MARTIN ELLIOT NEVER MENTIONED
HIS WIFE WAS EXPECTING.

04:37.044 --> 04:38.910
NO, MA'AM.

04:38.912 --> 04:41.113
WHY WOULD HE NOT SAY ANYTHING
ABOUT THE DEATH OF HIS CHILD?

04:42.015 --> 04:44.049
YES?
CAN I HELP YOU?

04:44.051 --> 04:45.817
SORRY. I THOUGHT
YOU'D BE DONE BY NOW.

04:45.819 --> 04:46.918
OH, GOD.

04:46.920 --> 04:48.920
PARDON ME.
I CAN'T BREATHE.

04:48.922 --> 04:52.491
Sharon: DR. MORALES, THIS IS,
UH, DEPUTY D.A. EMMA RIOS,

04:52.493 --> 04:54.026
WHO MAY BE CONFUSED.

04:54.028 --> 04:56.862
THIS HOMICIDE HAS NOTHING TO DO
WITH PHILLIP STROH.

04:56.864 --> 04:59.398
YES, BUT SINCE
I WAS COMING OVER TO INTERVIEW

04:59.400 --> 05:01.099
OUR MATERIAL WITNESS
IN THAT CASE,

05:01.101 --> 05:03.735
D.D.A. HOBBS THOUGHT I SHOULD
PICK UP THIS MURDER, TOO.

05:03.737 --> 05:05.470
OH, GOD.

05:05.472 --> 05:07.506
UH,
THE MASK WON'T HELP.

05:07.508 --> 05:09.941
JUST COLLECTS THE SMELL
IN ONE PLACE.

05:09.943 --> 05:11.510
HERE.

05:11.512 --> 05:14.513
PUT A LITTLE BIT OF THIS
UNDERNEATH YOUR NOSE.

05:14.515 --> 05:15.881
WHY DON'T YOU
JUST TURN YOUR BACK,

05:15.883 --> 05:17.416
READ THROUGH
OUR CRIME REPORT,

05:17.418 --> 05:20.052
AND JUST <i>LISTEN</i>
<i>TO DR. MORALES, OKAY?</i>

05:21.454 --> 05:23.655
THANK YOU, CAPTAIN.

05:23.657 --> 05:24.923
OKAY.

05:24.925 --> 05:27.859
HERE'S A CLEAN ENTRY WOUND
I CAN MEASURE.

05:27.861 --> 05:29.928
D.D.A. RIOS, YOU MAY WANT
TO COVER YOUR EARS.

05:31.531 --> 05:33.198
[ SQUISHING ]

05:36.436 --> 05:40.105
LOOKS LIKE A SINGLE-EDGE,
3-INCH-LONG BLADE.

05:40.107 --> 05:43.909
AND SHE WAS ATTACKED LYING DOWN
FROM BEHIND.

05:43.911 --> 05:46.545
I DON'T SEE DEFENSIVE WOUNDS,
THOUGH SHE COULD'VE BEEN ASLEEP.

05:46.547 --> 05:47.646
UNLESS SHE WAS DRUNK.

05:47.648 --> 05:49.848
NO.
SHE WAS PREGNANT.

05:49.850 --> 05:52.451
MAYBE HER HUSBAND DRUGGED HER,
BUT WITH WHAT?

05:52.453 --> 05:56.154
AS ALWAYS, TOX SCREENS GO FASTER
IF I KNOW WHAT TO LOOK FOR.

05:56.156 --> 05:57.756
Emma: EXCUSE ME,

05:57.758 --> 06:00.025
BUT WHAT IN THIS CRIME REPORT
SAYS "HUSBAND" TO YOU?

06:00.027 --> 06:04.563
WELL, THE KILLER
HAD ACCESS TO THE HOUSE.

06:06.799 --> 06:09.868
AND THE KNIFE
WE FOUND IN THE POOL...

06:09.870 --> 06:11.470
Tao: ...MATCHES EXACTLY
THE MEASUREMENTS

06:11.472 --> 06:14.740
OF THE MURDER WEAPON
AND FITS INTO THIS SPACE

06:14.742 --> 06:17.709
FROM THIS SET OF KNIVES
FROM THE VICTIM'S KITCHEN.

06:17.711 --> 06:19.778
ANY BIOLOGICAL EVIDENCE
ON THAT KNIFE?

06:19.780 --> 06:23.215
IT WAS DUMPED
IN A CHLORINATED POOL, SO NO.

06:24.550 --> 06:26.251
YOUR TIME-OF-DEATH WINDOW
ALLOWS OUR SUSPECT

06:26.253 --> 06:28.487
TO CLAIM HE WAS AWAY FROM HOME
DURING THE MURDER.

06:28.489 --> 06:29.755
DO YOU HAVE ANY OTHER REASON
TO HOLD HIM?

06:29.757 --> 06:31.256
Sharon:
WE'RE NOT HOLDING HIM.

06:31.258 --> 06:33.258
MR. ELLIOT'S HOUSE
IS A CRIME SCENE.

06:33.260 --> 06:35.527
HE'S HELPING US
FIND HIS WIFE'S KILLER.

06:35.529 --> 06:37.095
BUT YOU STILL ONLY HAVE
48 HOURS

06:37.097 --> 06:39.264
BEFORE YOU HAVE TO RELEASE HIM
OR PUT HIM IN FRONT OF A JUDGE.

06:39.266 --> 06:40.832
DO YOU EVEN HAVE A MOTIVE?

06:40.834 --> 06:42.033
Provenza: LOOK,
I KNOW IT'S OLD-FASHIONED,

06:42.035 --> 06:43.869
BUT WHY DON'T
WE JUST ASK HIM

06:43.871 --> 06:45.504
WHY HE STABBED HIS WIFE
TO DEATH?

06:45.506 --> 06:48.874
THERE ARE OTHER QUESTIONS
WE NEED ANSWERED FIRST.

06:48.876 --> 06:51.009
SORRY IT TOOK SO LONG.
OUR PRINTER'S DOWN AGAIN.

06:51.011 --> 06:52.778
WELL,
JUST KEEP USING TAYLOR'S

06:52.780 --> 06:54.780
UNTIL HE AUTHORIZES
A REPLACEMENT.

06:54.782 --> 06:57.048
HERE'S THE INCOMPLETE
PRESS RELEASE YOU ASKED
ME FOR, CAPTAIN,

06:57.050 --> 06:58.650
ALONG WITH
THE SUSPECT'S WEEKLY SCHEDULE,

06:58.652 --> 06:59.785
COURTESY OF HIS OFFICE.

06:59.787 --> 07:01.052
WAIT A MINUTE. WAIT.

07:01.054 --> 07:02.754
YOU'RE NOT SHARING
OUR PRESS RELEASE

07:02.756 --> 07:04.556
WITH MR. ELLIOT, ARE YOU?

07:04.558 --> 07:07.526
YES, D.D.A. RIOS,
THAT'S <i>EXACTLY</i> WHAT I'M DOING.

07:07.528 --> 07:09.728
[ RADIO CHATTER ]

07:10.930 --> 07:14.666
WHILE I'M DIRECTING,
MY SCHEDULE CHANGES CONSTANTLY.

07:14.668 --> 07:18.570
MY ASSISTANT PUTS OUT UPDATES
TO ME, MY AGENT, MY EDITOR,

07:18.572 --> 07:20.605
MY WIFE, MY EX-WIFE,

07:20.607 --> 07:21.606
MY MOTHER.

07:21.608 --> 07:23.074
CAPTAIN?
HMM?

07:23.076 --> 07:24.810
HERE'S THE PRESS RELEASE
YOU ASKED FOR.

07:24.812 --> 07:25.844
PRESS RELEASE?

07:25.846 --> 07:28.280
MR. ELLIOT, WE THINK

07:28.282 --> 07:30.282
THAT THE PERSON
THAT MURDERED YOUR WIFE

07:30.284 --> 07:32.684
MIGHT HAVE ACTUALLY
BEEN TRYING TO KILL <i>YOU.</i>

07:32.686 --> 07:34.920
OH, MY GOD.
MM-HMM.

07:34.922 --> 07:36.888
OH, MY GOD.
YOU MEAN...

07:36.890 --> 07:39.224
YOU MAY HAVE BEEN
THE INTENDED VICTIM, SIR, YES.

07:39.226 --> 07:43.028
AND OUR...CELEBRITY THREAT
DIVISION IS WORKING ON THAT.

07:43.030 --> 07:44.329
SO FROM HERE ON OUT,

07:44.331 --> 07:46.865
HOW WE TALK TO THE MEDIA
IS VERY IMPORTANT.

07:46.867 --> 07:48.166
LOOK OVER
THE PRESS RELEASE.

07:48.168 --> 07:49.935
MAKE SURE
WE'RE ALL ON THE SAME PAGE.

07:54.106 --> 07:56.975
WELL, YOU COULD LEAVE OUT
THE NAME OF THE FILM.

07:56.977 --> 07:58.076
[ CHUCKLES ]

07:58.078 --> 07:59.711
[ SCRIBBLING ]

07:59.713 --> 08:01.613
AND LET'S SAY
I'M "WORKING WITH THE L.A.P.D."

08:01.615 --> 08:03.582
INSTEAD OF "COOPERATING."

08:03.584 --> 08:06.585
[ Chuckling ]
"COOPERATING" MAKES ME
SOUND LIKE I'M A SUSPECT.

08:06.587 --> 08:10.589
DO NOT MENTION MY TWO SONS
"FROM A PREVIOUS MARRIAGE."

08:10.591 --> 08:11.723
MAN!

08:11.725 --> 08:13.358
I HAVE GOT TO TALK
WITH THEM.

08:13.360 --> 08:16.161
AND WHERE I WAS LAST NIGHT
IS LEFT BLANK. WHY?

08:16.163 --> 08:17.629
THIS SHOULD BE
"WATCHING DAILIES."

08:17.631 --> 08:19.331
Sanchez:
HOW DID WE MISS THAT?

08:19.333 --> 08:20.966
AND THAT WAS
WHAT TIME, SIR?

08:20.968 --> 08:22.801
7:00 TO 10:00.
IT'S ON MY SCHEDULE.

08:22.803 --> 08:24.703
CALL POSTPRODUCTION. THEY'LL
HAVE A RECORD OF THE DOWNLOAD.

08:25.671 --> 08:27.305
ANYONE WATCH THESE DAILIES
WITH YOU?

08:27.307 --> 08:28.974
NOT USUALLY,

08:28.976 --> 08:30.809
BUT I HAVE AN ACTRESS
WITH SOME BAD HABITS.

08:30.811 --> 08:33.278
I WANTED HER TO SEE HOW MUCH
SHE BLINKS HER EYES ON-CAMERA.

08:33.280 --> 08:34.813
WHY?

08:34.815 --> 08:37.349
Sharon: MR. ELLIOT,
WHEN THIS ACTRESS LEFT,

08:37.351 --> 08:40.819
SHE MAY HAVE SEEN SOMEONE
HANGING AROUND WAITING FOR YOU.

08:40.821 --> 08:42.153
COULD WE HAVE
HER PHONE NUMBER?

08:42.155 --> 08:44.055
YOUR PEOPLE WOULD NOT LET ME
BACK IN MY HOME

08:44.057 --> 08:45.690
TO GET MY CELL.

08:45.692 --> 08:47.626
I DON'T CARRY THESE NUMBERS
AROUND IN MY HEAD.

08:47.628 --> 08:49.694
WE'LL FIND THAT PHONE
FOR YOU, SIR.

08:50.696 --> 08:53.999
OH, MY GOD.
OH, MY GOD.

08:54.001 --> 08:55.800
SO MUCH LOST.

08:55.802 --> 08:57.736
THERE'S ANOTHER CHANCE
AT BEING A GOOD HUSBAND,

08:57.738 --> 08:59.638
ANOTHER CHANCE
AT BEING A GOOD FATHER.

08:59.640 --> 09:00.972
WHAT HAPPENED?

09:00.974 --> 09:03.942
ANOTHER...CHANCE
AT BEING A GOOD FATHER?

09:03.944 --> 09:06.811
EXCUSE ME, SIR. ARE YOU SAYING
YOUR WIFE WAS PREGNANT?

09:06.813 --> 09:08.647
YES.

09:08.649 --> 09:10.081
OHHH.

09:10.083 --> 09:12.117
YES. DID I NOT MENTION THAT
BEFORE? I CAN'T REMEMBER.

09:12.119 --> 09:14.119
HOW COULD I HAVE
FORGOTTEN THAT?

09:15.254 --> 09:16.821
[ SIGHS ]

09:16.823 --> 09:19.991
EVERYTHING WAS SUPPOSED TO BE
DIFFERENT THIS TIME.

09:19.993 --> 09:21.159
MY KIDS.

09:21.161 --> 09:22.961
I HAVE GOT TO TALK
TO MY KIDS.

09:22.963 --> 09:26.197
<i>BECAUSE, ASHLEY,</i>
<i>THEY'RE</i> MY <i>KIDS, TOO.</i>

09:26.199 --> 09:27.699
<i>WHAT --</i>

09:27.701 --> 09:28.934
<i>I KNOW THAT.</i>
<i>I UNDERSTAND THAT.</i>

09:28.936 --> 09:31.269
AH. NEGOTIATING
WITH THE EX-WIFE.

09:31.271 --> 09:34.339
YOU KNOW, MAYBE
THE FORMER MRS. ELLIOT

09:34.341 --> 09:36.341
WOULD BE WILLING
TO SHARE SOME MEMORIES

09:36.343 --> 09:38.977
OF HER TIME
SPENT WITH THE ARTISTE.

09:38.979 --> 09:42.080
JUST GET THEM OUT OF THE HOUSE,
<i>GET THEM HERE.</i>

09:42.082 --> 09:43.982
Emma: I STILL SAY
GIVING HIM HIS PHONE IS RISKY.

09:43.984 --> 09:45.784
WHAT IF HE CALLS
A LAWYER?

09:45.786 --> 09:48.353
IS SHE THE NEW, UH...
WHAT IS IT?

09:48.355 --> 09:50.689
DEPUTY D.A.
THAT'S HER.

09:50.691 --> 09:52.324
HMM.
WHAT'S SHE LIKE?

09:53.793 --> 09:55.961
LIEUTENANT PROVENZA AND I
WILL BOTH BE WITH YOU

09:55.963 --> 09:57.195
FOR THE INTERVIEW.

09:57.197 --> 09:59.364
[  <i>DIALING</i>]
OH, MAN. THAT BAD?

09:59.366 --> 10:01.433
Elliot: <i>YEAH, HI, SWEETIE.</i>
<i>HEY, CAPTAIN,</i>
<i>I THINK THIS IS IT.</i>

10:01.435 --> 10:03.134
<i>LISTEN -- UH, THANKS.</i>

10:03.136 --> 10:05.236
<i>I-I'M NOT SAYING</i>
<i>THAT THIS IS GOING TO HAPPEN,</i>

10:05.238 --> 10:08.807
<i>BUT IF THE POLICE CALL YOU,</i>
<i>I NEED YOU TO TELL THEM</i>

10:08.809 --> 10:11.009
<i>THAT I WAS WITH YOU</i>
<i>LAST NIGHT.</i>

10:11.011 --> 10:13.311
I'LL DRAW UP A WARRANT TO GET
THE NUMBER HE JUST CALLED.

10:15.047 --> 10:16.715
Provenza:
BIG SURPRISE.

10:16.717 --> 10:19.150
OUR SUSPECT
SEEMS TO HAVE A GIRLFRIEND.

10:19.152 --> 10:22.988
IN OTHER NEWS THIS MORNING,
THE SUN ROSE IN THE EAST.

10:22.990 --> 10:24.723
WELL, IT CERTAINLY
DIDN'T SOUND LIKE

10:24.725 --> 10:26.191
HE WAS GRIEVING
HIS WIFE AND CHILD.

10:26.193 --> 10:27.826
<i>OKAY.</i>

10:27.828 --> 10:30.428
NOPE. SOUNDS LIKE A MAN
WHO KNOWS HE'S A SUSPECT.

10:30.430 --> 10:32.364
<i>I'LL TELL YOU LATER.</i>
<i>BYE.</i>

10:43.843 --> 10:45.276
IN YOUR WRITTEN STATEMENT
TFROM LAST YEAR,PART.

10:45.278 --> 10:49.147
YOU SAY "MR. STROH
WAS ABOUT 100 FEET AWAY."

10:49.149 --> 10:51.149
RIGHT. HE WAS
<i>ABOUT</i> 100 FEET AWAY.

10:52.218 --> 10:53.785
ABOUT.

10:53.787 --> 10:55.020
AND YOU SAW THE KILLER

10:55.022 --> 10:57.055
WHEN YOU WERE WITH
A MR. DOUGLAS GRAND,

10:57.057 --> 10:59.491
STANDING
IN YOUR UNDERWEAR.

11:03.295 --> 11:04.462
YES.

11:04.464 --> 11:06.498
AND YOU WERE
IN YOUR UNDERWEAR WHY?

11:07.933 --> 11:09.367
IT WAS HOT OUTSIDE.

11:10.903 --> 11:12.937
WHAT HE WAS WEARING
IS PERTINENT BECAUSE...?

11:12.939 --> 11:13.972
I'LL GET TO THAT.

11:13.974 --> 11:15.774
THIS HILLTOP --

11:15.776 --> 11:18.343
WAS IT A FAVORITE SPOT OF YOURS
TO BRINGS JOHNS OR CLIENTS?

11:18.345 --> 11:20.378
OKAY,
THE WORD IS "DATE,"

11:20.380 --> 11:22.414
AND I DIDN'T HAVE
A FAVORITE SPOT, OKAY, LADY?

11:22.416 --> 11:23.982
THIS WASN'T, LIKE, FUN
FOR ME.

11:23.984 --> 11:25.450
IT WAS DOUG'S SPOT,
NOT MINE,

11:25.452 --> 11:27.819
AND HE LIKED IT
BECAUSE IT WAS OFF THE TRAIL.

11:27.821 --> 11:29.354
I DON'T KNOW.
ASK <i>HIM</i> ABOUT IT.

11:29.356 --> 11:31.489
DO YOU REALLY NEED TO PURSUE
THIS LINE OF QUESTIONING?

11:31.491 --> 11:33.992
MR. STROH'S LAWYERS
WILL FOCUS

11:33.994 --> 11:36.294
ON WHY RUSTY WAS
AT GRIFFITH PARK AT NIGHT

11:36.296 --> 11:38.263
ENGAGED IN AN ACT
OF SEX FOR HIRE

11:38.265 --> 11:40.065
IN ORDER TO DISCREDIT
HIS TESTIMONY.

11:40.067 --> 11:42.200
YOU THINK <i>I'M</i> TOUGH?

11:42.202 --> 11:44.936
WAIT UNTIL THE DEFENSE ASKS IF
YOU HAD A THING FOR OLDER GUYS.

11:44.938 --> 11:46.271
[ SCOFFS ]

11:46.273 --> 11:48.339
OR WHY YOU ENDED UP
ON THE STREET OR HOW IT WAS

11:48.341 --> 11:50.341
YOU BECAME A "WHOREPHAN"
IN THE FIRST PLACE.

11:50.343 --> 11:52.077
I'M SORRY --
A-A-A "WHOREPHAN"?!

11:52.079 --> 11:54.212
OH, THEY'LL SAY IT.
D.D.A. RIOS,
WE ARE STOPPING!

11:54.214 --> 11:56.214
EXCUSE ME,
BUT I AM NOT REQUIRED

11:56.216 --> 11:58.149
WE NEED TO STOP!
TO INCLUDE OFFICERS
IN THIS INTERVIEW.

11:58.151 --> 12:01.219
RUSTY HAS THE RIGHT
TO HAVE HIS GUARDIAN PRESENT!

12:03.355 --> 12:04.889
HIS GUARDIAN?

12:04.891 --> 12:08.526
A-ARE YOU SAYING
MY -- MY WITNESS LIVES WITH YOU?

12:08.528 --> 12:10.228
RUSTY,
THAT'S ENOUGH FOR NOW.

12:10.230 --> 12:11.296
LIEUTENANT, THANK YOU.

12:12.832 --> 12:16.000
HEY, YOU ARE AN ASSHOLE.

12:16.002 --> 12:17.368
OKAY?

12:17.370 --> 12:19.003
AND I AM NEVER
TALKING TO YOU AGAIN. NEVER.

12:25.511 --> 12:28.980
THERE'S NOTHING IN EITHER
L.A.P.D. RULES OR POLICY

12:28.982 --> 12:31.516
THAT SAYS RUSTY CAN'T LIVE
WITH A POLICE OFFICER.

12:31.518 --> 12:34.252
STROH'S LAWYERS WILL CLAIM
YOU COACHED THE CHILD.

12:34.254 --> 12:36.855
I'VE NEVER DISCUSSED THE CASE
WITH RUSTY EVEN ONCE.

12:36.857 --> 12:39.124
NO, YOU JUST
PUT A ROOF OVER HIS HEAD,

12:39.126 --> 12:40.925
FED HIM,
AND BOUGHT HIM HIS CLOTHES.

12:40.927 --> 12:42.193
ARE YOU PAYING
FOR THE CATHOLIC SCHOOL

12:42.195 --> 12:43.461
THAT GOES WITH THE UNIFORM
HE'S WEARING?

12:43.463 --> 12:45.130
AND WERE THOSE KEYS
TO A VEHICLE

12:45.132 --> 12:47.031
HE JUST GRABBED
OFF YOUR DESK?

12:47.033 --> 12:48.900
I KEEP A CAR
FOR WHEN MY KIDS VISIT,

12:48.902 --> 12:51.002
AND RUSTY TAKES IT
TO SCHOOL.

12:51.004 --> 12:53.304
OH, I APOLOGIZE.
YOU'RE NOT COACHING THE WITNESS.

12:53.306 --> 12:54.405
YOU'RE <i>BRIBING</i> HIM.

12:54.407 --> 12:56.341
THIS HAS TO CHANGE.

12:56.343 --> 13:00.011
BUT FIRST, I NEED HIM
TO FINISH THIS INTERVIEW.

13:00.013 --> 13:02.213
IT'S NOT A GOOD IDEA
RIGHT NOW.

13:02.215 --> 13:03.281
OH, MY GOD.

13:03.283 --> 13:04.949
HMM?
WHAT EVER HAPPENED

13:04.951 --> 13:07.886
TO PROFESSIONAL DISTANCE
AND GOOD OLD FOSTER CARE?

13:07.888 --> 13:10.321
THAT BOY WAS SELLING HIMSELF
ON THE STREET TO SURVIVE,

13:10.323 --> 13:12.924
WHICH PUTS HIM
AT SPECIAL RISK --

13:12.926 --> 13:15.960
DON'T TALK TO ME
ABOUT --
DON'T INTERRUPT ME.

13:16.929 --> 13:20.198
IT PUTS HIM AT SPECIAL RISK
FOR SUICIDE.

13:20.200 --> 13:22.333
DON'T TALK TO ME
ABOUT SPECIAL RISKS

13:22.335 --> 13:24.636
WHEN I AM PROSECUTING
A SERIAL KILLER.

13:26.172 --> 13:28.573
I WANT THAT BOY
OUT OF YOUR HOUSE

13:28.575 --> 13:31.643
AND PLACED SOMEWHERE ELSE
POSTHASTE.

13:31.645 --> 13:33.511
THAT'S NOT GONNA HAPPEN.

13:33.513 --> 13:36.614
AND I SUGGEST YOU FACTOR
MY LEGAL GUARDIANSHIP

13:36.616 --> 13:37.916
INTO YOUR CASE.

13:37.918 --> 13:40.618
OH...I <i>AM.</i>

13:40.620 --> 13:42.520
AND IN JUST THE SAME WAY
YOU'RE FACTORING IN

13:42.522 --> 13:45.223
HOW YOUR SUSPECT
NEVER TOLD YOU ABOUT HIS BABY.

13:45.225 --> 13:47.258
Elliot: NO.

13:47.260 --> 13:49.627
WELL,
THEY'RE NOT EXACTLY...

13:49.629 --> 13:52.597
Tao: I CAN'T TELL YOU WHO HE WAS
ASKING TO LIE FOR HIM,

13:52.599 --> 13:54.132
BECAUSE ELLIOT
WAS CALLING <i>HIMSELF.</i>

13:54.134 --> 13:55.533
THE NUMBER HE DIALED
FOR HIS ALIBI

13:55.535 --> 13:58.069
BELONGED TO HIS OWN CORPORATION,
RIVERWAY FILMS.

13:58.071 --> 14:00.004
HE ORDERED ANOTHER CELL
FOR HIS COMPANY

14:00.006 --> 14:01.272
AND GAVE IT TO SOMEONE.

14:01.274 --> 14:02.507
Sykes: MEANWHILE,
ON OUR VICTIM'S PHONE,

14:02.509 --> 14:04.275
STARTING EIGHT HOURS
BEFORE GRETCHEN ELLIOT

14:04.277 --> 14:05.944
WAS FOUND
AT THE BOTTOM OF HER POOL,

14:05.946 --> 14:09.147
SHE HAD A CALL FROM HER MOM,
A CALL TO A CATERER,

14:09.149 --> 14:11.382
A LATE-AFTERNOON CALL
FROM THE HOTEL PERINO --

14:11.384 --> 14:12.650
NO ROOM NUMBER --

14:12.652 --> 14:14.285
AND THEN
ABOUT A HALF AN HOUR AFTER THAT,

14:14.287 --> 14:16.120
SHE MADE AN APPOINTMENT
FOR FRIDAY AT HER HAIR SALON.

14:16.122 --> 14:17.689
CAPTAIN.

14:17.691 --> 14:20.291
ELLIOT'S STILL RESCHEDULING
ACTORS AND CREW FOR HIS FILM.

14:20.293 --> 14:22.527
Tao: SEEMS LIKE
HE HAS MORE OF A RELATIONSHIP

14:22.529 --> 14:24.429
WITH HIS MOVIE
THAN HIS WIFE.

14:24.431 --> 14:26.231
NO USE TALKING TO
THOSE PEOPLE. THEY HAVE TO
STAY ON HIS GOOD SIDE.

14:26.233 --> 14:29.500
FLYNN'S ON HIS WAY UP
WITH ELLIOT'S EX-WIFE.

14:29.502 --> 14:32.437
NOW, IF MY EXPERIENCE
MEANS ANYTHING,

14:32.439 --> 14:35.673
THEN SHE WON'T EVEN <i>REMEMBER</i>
<i>HIS GOOD SIDE.</i>

14:35.675 --> 14:39.978
AND IF ELLIOT WAS CHEATING
ON HIS CURRENT WIFE, WHICH --

14:39.980 --> 14:41.379
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

14:43.983 --> 14:45.283
Tao: HMM.

14:45.285 --> 14:48.219
EX-WIFE LOOKS FAMILIAR.

14:48.221 --> 14:50.655
SAME SIZE AND SHAPE
AS THE VICTIM.

14:50.657 --> 14:52.190
BLOND, FIT.

14:52.192 --> 14:54.325
I BET
SHE'S GOT BLUE EYES.

14:54.327 --> 14:55.393
THE GUY HAS A TYPE.

14:55.395 --> 14:57.128
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

14:57.130 --> 15:00.531
ASHLEY.
I'M CAPTAIN SHARON RAYDOR.

15:00.533 --> 15:03.468
SO SORRY
ABOUT YOU AND YOUR FAMILY.

15:03.470 --> 15:05.336
YEAH.
NOT A GOOD TIME.

15:05.338 --> 15:07.672
REPORTERS OUTSIDE OUR HOUSE
AT 6:00 A.M.

15:07.674 --> 15:09.274
TRYING TO TALK
TO MY SONS.

15:09.276 --> 15:12.477
AND THEY LOVED, LOVED, <i>LOVED</i>
<i>GRETCHEN.</i>

15:14.580 --> 15:18.616
MR. ELLIOT HAS BEEN
VERY CONCERNED ABOUT YOUR BOYS.

15:19.685 --> 15:22.020
THAT'S...GOOD TO HEAR.

15:22.022 --> 15:24.489
SOMETIMES I THINK
THEY SHOULD BE RE-INTRODUCED.

15:24.491 --> 15:27.425
YOU MEAN YOUR KIDS DON'T SEE
THEIR FATHER VERY OFTEN?

15:27.427 --> 15:28.760
TECHNICALLY,
EVERY OTHER WEEKEND,

15:28.762 --> 15:30.628
AND IN THE SUMMER,
THEY LIVE IN HIS POOL.

15:30.630 --> 15:34.666
BUT MARTIN'S NEVER AROUND --
ALWAYS DIRECTING OR DEVELOPING.

15:34.668 --> 15:37.602
DID HE DEVELOP A LOT
DURING YOUR MARRIAGE, TOO?

15:37.604 --> 15:41.105
TAKE A LOT OF "MEETINGS"
AT NIGHT?

15:43.575 --> 15:44.809
I SEE.

15:44.811 --> 15:46.511
WAS HE CHEATING
ON GRETCHEN, TOO?

15:46.513 --> 15:47.779
MM-HMM.

15:49.148 --> 15:50.715
WHY AM I
NOT SURPRISED?

15:50.717 --> 15:52.817
MR. ELLIOT
CHEATED ON YOU?

15:52.819 --> 15:55.186
BOTH TIMES
I WAS "WITH CHILD."

15:55.188 --> 15:57.455
SO, OF COURSE,
HE DID IT TO GRETCHEN, TOO.

15:57.457 --> 15:59.057
HE'S INCAPABLE OF CHANGE.

15:59.059 --> 16:01.292
SO, HE LEFT YOU
FOR GRETCHEN.

16:01.294 --> 16:04.262
SIX YEARS AGO,
DURING MY SECOND PREGNANCY.

16:04.264 --> 16:05.396
YES.

16:05.398 --> 16:07.065
I NEVER BLAMED HER,
THOUGH.

16:07.067 --> 16:09.334
GRETCHEN GOT HER RING
THE SAME WAY <i>I</i> DID.

16:09.336 --> 16:10.635
OH?

16:10.637 --> 16:13.137
MR. ELLIOT WAS MARRIED
WHEN <i>YOU</i> MET HIM?

16:13.139 --> 16:14.839
YES.

16:14.841 --> 16:17.475
HIS FIRST WIFE, BRITTANY,
COMMITTED SUICIDE.

16:17.477 --> 16:20.211
LOOK, I'M NOT SURE WHERE YOU'RE
GOING WITH THESE QUESTIONS,

16:20.213 --> 16:22.413
BUT MARTIN DOESN'T HAVE TO KILL
HIS WIVES.

16:22.415 --> 16:25.350
TRUST ME --
HE HAS GREAT DIVORCE LAWYERS.

16:25.352 --> 16:28.553
E-EXCUSE ME. RIGHT NOW
I'M WORRIED ABOUT MY BOYS.

16:36.161 --> 16:37.662
THE FIRST WIFE?

16:39.164 --> 16:41.432
Tao: BRITTANY WELLS
MARRIED MARTIN ELLIOT

16:41.434 --> 16:44.268
ALMOST 20 YEARS AGO
BUT KEPT HER OWN LAST NAME.

16:44.270 --> 16:47.572
YEAH, THAT WAS BEFORE
HE BECAME <i>THE</i> MARTIN ELLIOT.

16:47.574 --> 16:51.576
HERE'S THE FIRST MRS. ELLIOT'S
PROFESSIONAL POSE.

16:51.578 --> 16:53.511
AH.

16:53.513 --> 16:56.180
AND HERE'S
WHAT SHE LOOKED LIKE

16:56.182 --> 17:00.118
WHEN THE L.A.P.D. MET HER
15 YEARS AGO.

17:00.120 --> 17:01.652
Sanchez:
WELL, IT SAYS HERE

17:01.654 --> 17:04.389
ELLIOT FOUND THE BODY
WHEN HE CAME HOME FROM WORK.

17:04.391 --> 17:05.523
HE'S FAMOUS FOR SEQUELS.

17:05.525 --> 17:07.625
YOUR DIVISION
HAS TO STOP USING

17:07.627 --> 17:09.727
THE PRINTER IN MY OFFICE,
CAPTAIN.

17:09.729 --> 17:12.563
WELL, IT'S THE ONLY ONE WORKING
ON THE ENTIRE FLOOR,

17:12.565 --> 17:14.632
AND WE USED IT
FOR A SEARCH WARRANT.

17:14.634 --> 17:16.534
WHICH WE ARE
<i>REALLY</i> GOING TO NEED,

17:16.536 --> 17:19.537
GIVEN WHERE THIS CASE
IS TAKING US.

17:19.539 --> 17:21.305
OH! EW!
IS THAT ANOTHER BODY?

17:21.307 --> 17:22.540
WHO'S DEAD <i>NOW?</i>

17:22.542 --> 17:24.709
UH, ELLIOT'S FIRST WIFE,
BRITTANY.

17:24.711 --> 17:26.244
WHO DIED PREGNANT

17:26.246 --> 17:27.879
AND CUT HER WRISTS
WITH THIS SMALL KNIFE

17:27.881 --> 17:30.615
AND HAD A POSITIVE TOX SCREEN
FOR VALIUM.

17:30.617 --> 17:32.617
Provenza: IF YOU'D BEEN
PAYING ATTENTION TO <i>THIS</i> CASE

17:32.619 --> 17:33.851
INSTEAD OF RUSTY BECK,

17:33.853 --> 17:36.154
THEN YOU WOULDN'T
BE PLAYING CATCH-UP NOW.

17:36.156 --> 17:38.289
Flynn: BECAUSE
IF DR. MORALES FINDS VALIUM

17:38.291 --> 17:40.558
IN GRETCHEN ELLIOT'S BODY,
WE HAVE A PATTERN.

17:40.560 --> 17:42.460
Provenza:
YEAH, THEN ALL WE NEED

17:42.462 --> 17:45.296
IS THE NAME OF THE ACTRESS
HE CALLED TO BE HIS ALIBI.

17:45.298 --> 17:47.165
ASK HIM THAT,
AND HE'LL INVOKE.

17:47.167 --> 17:48.933
NOT IF WE PRESENT
THE INFORMATION PROPERLY.

17:48.935 --> 17:50.001
LIEUTENANT.

17:51.170 --> 17:52.703
THE KILLER HAD ACCESS
TO YOUR SCHEDULE,

17:52.705 --> 17:53.905
KNEW YOUR ALARM CODE,

17:53.907 --> 17:56.307
USED A KNIFE
FROM <i>YOUR</i> KITCHEN,

17:56.309 --> 17:57.742
A HOSE
FROM <i>YOUR</i> BACKYARD.

17:57.744 --> 17:59.744
ALL THESE THINGS
POINT IN ONE DIRECTION.

17:59.746 --> 18:01.512
<i>THIS</i> DIRECTION.

18:02.848 --> 18:03.915
ME?!

18:04.516 --> 18:05.883
<i>SERIOUSLY?</i>

18:05.885 --> 18:07.852
<i>THE COMPUTER LOG-ONS</i>
<i>FOR THE DAY...</i>

18:07.854 --> 18:09.287
Tao: <i>PROVE NOTHING.</i>

18:09.289 --> 18:10.888
YOU COULD HAVE DONE ALL THAT
FROM HOME,

18:10.890 --> 18:12.957
KILLED YOUR WIFE,
LOGGED OFF A FEW HOURS LATER.

18:12.959 --> 18:15.259
YOU SAID YOU WERE
WITH AN ACTRESS AT THE TIME?

18:17.496 --> 18:18.496
ALL RIGHT.

18:18.498 --> 18:19.897
FINE. YES.

18:19.899 --> 18:21.365
[ SMACKS LIPS ]

18:21.367 --> 18:22.700
CALL JENNIFER O'BRIEN.

18:22.702 --> 18:24.469
SHE'LL COOPERATE WITH YOU,
<i>I'M SURE.</i>

18:24.471 --> 18:25.903
<i>I BET SHE WILL, TOO,</i>
<i>SINCE WE HAVE YOU ON VIDEO</i>

18:25.905 --> 18:27.271
<i>ASKING HER TO LIE.</i>

18:28.307 --> 18:29.941
YOU RECORDED
MY PRIVATE CONVERSATION?

18:29.943 --> 18:31.209
WITHOUT MY CONSENT?

18:31.211 --> 18:32.777
Flynn: OH, PLEASE.

18:32.779 --> 18:35.713
SUDDENLY, MR. "I MAKE REALITY
COP SHOWS" DOESN'T REMEMBER

18:35.715 --> 18:38.683
THAT THERE'S NO RIGHT TO PRIVACY
IN A POLICE STATION?

18:38.685 --> 18:40.818
OF COURSE WE RECORDED YOU.
WHAT DO YOU THINK? WE'RE IDIOTS?

18:42.488 --> 18:43.654
<i>I WANT MY LAWYER</i> NOW.

18:43.656 --> 18:45.289
Tao:
<i>THAT'S YOUR RIGHT, SIR.</i>

18:45.291 --> 18:47.492
AND THERE GOES
MILLIONS OF DOLLARS UP IN SMOKE

18:47.494 --> 18:49.794
IN A FIVE-YEAR
DEATH-PENALTY TRIAL.

18:49.796 --> 18:52.763
HIS EGO WON'T PERMIT IT.

18:52.765 --> 18:54.632
Tao: <i>JUST KNOW -- THE SECOND</i>
<i>YOU CALL AN ATTORNEY</i>

18:54.634 --> 18:56.667
<i>AND INVOKE YOUR RIGHTS...</i>

18:56.669 --> 18:59.237
I'LL BE ARRESTING YOU
FOR MULTIPLE MURDERS
IN THE FIRST DEGREE

18:59.239 --> 19:01.239
WITH SPECIAL CIRCUMSTANCES.

19:01.241 --> 19:03.774
Sykes:
AND THE VIDEO OF YOUR TRIP
TO THE COUNTY JAIL

19:03.776 --> 19:05.309
WILL GO
STRAIGHT TO YouTube,

19:05.311 --> 19:06.777
WHERE IT WILL LIVE
UNTIL THE DAY YOU DIE.

19:06.779 --> 19:09.380
SO BE SURE
AND SMILE AT THE CAMERA.

19:09.382 --> 19:11.349
<i>OR YOU CAN HELP US</i>
<i>USE THIS SEARCH WARRANT.</i>

19:11.351 --> 19:13.651
Elliot: <i>IS THIS WHAT YOU MEANT</i>
<i>BY "CELEBRITY THREAT DIVISION"?</i>

19:13.653 --> 19:15.853
'CAUSE I'M FEELING
PRETTY THREATENED RIGHT NOW.

19:20.592 --> 19:22.560
ALL RIGHT. FINE.

19:22.562 --> 19:23.694
SEARCH MY HOUSE.

19:23.696 --> 19:24.996
YOU'RE NOT GONNA FIND
ANYTHING!

19:24.998 --> 19:27.265
OH, WE'RE NOT SEARCHING
YOUR <i>HOUSE.</i>

19:27.267 --> 19:29.534
JUST UNDER
YOUR FINGERNAILS.

19:29.536 --> 19:32.370
LOOKING FOR A LITTLE BLOOD.

19:32.372 --> 19:33.671
Emma: OKAY.

19:33.673 --> 19:36.274
I'M GONNA GO REVIEW
THIS NEW MATERIAL.

19:36.276 --> 19:40.611
BUT I WANT SOME ASSURANCES
ON MY OTHER ISSUES.

19:45.484 --> 19:46.851
Elliot: <i>OKAY.</i>

19:46.853 --> 19:49.387
<i>OKAY, LOOK...</i>

19:49.389 --> 19:51.489
<i>I ADMIT IT.</i>

19:51.491 --> 19:52.690
<i>I FABRICATED AN ALIBI.</i>

19:52.692 --> 19:54.525
<i>BUT ONLY BECAUSE I KNOW</i>

19:54.527 --> 19:56.627
<i>THAT THE POLICE ALWAYS</i>
<i>CONCENTRATE ON THE HUSBAND.</i>

19:56.629 --> 20:00.765
DO YOU HAVE CONFLICTS
BETWEEN YOUR JOB AS CAPTAIN

20:00.767 --> 20:04.035
AND BEING THE FOSTER PARENT
OF A MATERIAL WITNESS?

20:04.037 --> 20:05.303
<i>...POURED MYSELF A DRINK.</i>

20:05.305 --> 20:06.771
<i>I WOKE UP THREE HOURS LATER,</i>

20:06.773 --> 20:08.706
<i>AND THIS WAS A BAD NIGHT</i>
<i>FOR THAT TO HAPPEN.</i>

20:08.708 --> 20:10.575
<i>BUT YOU --</i>
<i>YOU CAN'T ARREST ME!</i>

20:11.577 --> 20:12.877
NO.

20:12.879 --> 20:15.313
MY ROLE IS THE SAME
IN BOTH INSTANCES --

20:15.315 --> 20:17.715
TO PROTECT THE CHILD.

20:17.717 --> 20:19.984
IF HE STOPS COOPERATING
WITH US,

20:19.986 --> 20:22.453
I'LL PUT THE BOY
BACK WITH DCFS,

20:22.455 --> 20:24.622
FIND HIM
ANOTHER FOSTER HOME.

20:24.624 --> 20:26.457
AND YOU SHOULD
TELL HIM THAT.

20:26.459 --> 20:28.759
THREATENING THE STABILITY
OF HIS ENVIRONMENT

20:28.761 --> 20:30.861
IS THE WORST THING
I COULD DO TO RUSTY.

20:30.863 --> 20:32.096
I CAN'T LOSE HIS TRUST.

20:32.098 --> 20:33.898
I JUST NEED
A LITTLE MORE TIME.

20:33.900 --> 20:36.400
I JUST BOUGHT YOU
24 HOURS.

20:36.402 --> 20:38.803
THE BOY SITS DOWN WITH EMMA
TOMORROW AFTERNOON,

20:38.805 --> 20:41.505
OR...HE'S GONE.

20:47.546 --> 20:48.546
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

20:55.520 --> 20:56.988
<i>"LITTLE CAT FEET," "BLACK CAT,"</i>
<i>AND "CAT IN THE BAG,"</i>

20:56.990 --> 20:58.656
<i>HAS BECOME</i>
<i>A PERSON OF INTEREST</i>

20:58.658 --> 20:59.991
<i>IN THE MURDER OF HIS WIFE,</i>

20:59.993 --> 21:01.859
<i>FOUND IN THE BOTTOM</i>
<i>OF THE POOL</i>

21:01.861 --> 21:03.794
<i>BEHIND THIS SPRAWLING</i>
<i>CONTEMPORARY HOME IN BEL-AIR.</i>

21:03.796 --> 21:05.062
I'M NOT EATING
ON THE COUCH.

21:05.064 --> 21:06.964
I'M EATING
IN   <i>FRON</i>OF THE COUCH.

21:06.966 --> 21:08.966
AND I'M HOLDING A PLATE
UNDERNEATH MY HAMBURGER,
JUST SO YOU KNOW.

21:08.968 --> 21:12.370
I'M WATCHING YOUR CASE
ON TELEVISION, SHARON.

21:12.372 --> 21:13.504
REALLY?
YEAH.

21:13.506 --> 21:14.905
AND THEY'RE ALL LIKE,

21:14.907 --> 21:18.409
"OH, THIS FAMOUS DIRECTOR GUY
KILLED HIS WIFE."

21:18.411 --> 21:19.577
WHY'D HE DO IT?

21:19.579 --> 21:21.379
SOMETIMES
IT'S ANOTHER WOMAN.

21:21.381 --> 21:22.747
[ TELEVISION TURNS OFF ]

21:22.749 --> 21:24.782
DIVORCE SETTLEMENTS
CAN BE <i>VERY</i> EXPENSIVE --

21:24.784 --> 21:26.117
CHILD SUPPORT
AND ALL THAT.

21:26.119 --> 21:29.086
BUT HE'S RICH ALREADY,
RIGHT?

21:29.088 --> 21:30.421
IS HE GONNA GET A DEAL?

21:30.423 --> 21:31.889
I DON'T KNOW.
WE'LL SEE.

21:31.891 --> 21:34.792
D.D.A. RIOS IS TURNING OUT
TO BE MORE COMPLICATED

21:34.794 --> 21:35.860
THAN I'D HOPED.

21:35.862 --> 21:38.596
YEAH.
TELL ME ABOUT IT.

21:38.598 --> 21:39.930
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

21:39.932 --> 21:42.066
SHE'S CRAZY,
THAT EMMA LADY.

21:42.068 --> 21:43.934
I'M DONE TALKING TO HER.

21:43.936 --> 21:47.471
BUT YOU HAVE TO TESTIFY
IN COURT.

21:47.473 --> 21:49.707
[ PLATE CLANKS ]

21:49.709 --> 21:50.841
WHY?

21:50.843 --> 21:52.543
BRENDA WAS THERE
THAT NIGHT.

21:52.545 --> 21:54.545
SHE CAN SAY WHAT HAPPENED,
CAN'T SHE?

21:54.547 --> 21:57.148
CHIEF JOHNSON WAS AT HER HOUSE.
SHE WASN'T AT THE PARK.

21:57.150 --> 21:59.750
YOU'RE THE ONLY PERSON
WHO WAS IN BOTH PLACES.

21:59.752 --> 22:01.419
OKAY, LISTEN --

22:01.421 --> 22:05.456
WE CAN'T DISCUSS ANYTHING
ABOUT YOUR TESTIMONY,

22:05.458 --> 22:06.891
BUT YOU SHOULD BE
AWARE --

22:06.893 --> 22:08.559
RUSTY, YOU --

22:08.561 --> 22:10.428
YOU SHOULD BE AWARE,
RUSTY --

22:10.430 --> 22:11.862
HEY, I AM <i>COMPLETELY</i> AWARE,
OKAY?

22:11.864 --> 22:13.831
I HAVE WAITED MY WHOLE LIFE
TO HAVE FRIENDS --

22:13.833 --> 22:15.533
MY WHOLE LIFE.

22:15.535 --> 22:17.568
AND THAT EMMA LADY IS
ABOUT TO TAKE THAT AWAY FROM ME,

22:17.570 --> 22:19.570
BECAUSE THAT IS WHAT WILL HAPPEN
WHEN PEOPLE FIND OUT

22:19.572 --> 22:20.971
WHAT I WAS DOING
UP AT GRIFFITH PARK.

22:20.973 --> 22:23.708
YOU WON'T HAVE TO ANSWER
THOSE QUESTIONS.

22:23.710 --> 22:24.975
SHE SAID
THAT THEY WOULD BE ASKED.

22:24.977 --> 22:26.610
I KNOW.
AND THEY WILL.

22:26.612 --> 22:28.012
BUT WHAT YOU WERE DOING
IN GRIFFITH PARK WAS ILLEGAL,

22:28.014 --> 22:32.149
SO IF THE SUBJECT
COMES UP...

22:32.151 --> 22:34.185
YOU CAN PLEAD THE FIFTH.

22:34.187 --> 22:35.986
PLEAD THE WHAT?

22:35.988 --> 22:38.789
ALL RIGHT, THE FIFTH AMENDMENT
TO THE CONSTITUTION

22:38.791 --> 22:41.459
LETS YOU REFUSE
TO SAY ANYTHING UNDER OATH

22:41.461 --> 22:43.527
THAT THE STATE CAN THEN USE
TO PROSECUTE YOU.

22:43.529 --> 22:46.464
THAT DOESN'T MEAN YOU SHOULD
KEEP ANY INFORMATION FROM --

22:46.466 --> 22:48.199
OH, MY GOD. YOU WANT ME
TO TALK TO HER AGAIN?

22:48.201 --> 22:50.468
THAT IS BULLSHIT,
SHARON!

22:50.470 --> 22:52.870
I AM THE WITNESS,
NOT THE CRIMINAL,

22:52.872 --> 22:55.005
AND THAT EMMA
IS ATTACKING <i>ME.</i>

22:56.675 --> 22:58.042
LET ME EXPLAIN TO YOU

22:58.044 --> 23:02.613
JUST HOW IMPORTANT YOU ARE
TO THIS PROCESS.

23:02.615 --> 23:06.784
A MAN WHO RAPED AND KILLED
FIVE YOUNG GIRLS

23:06.786 --> 23:09.620
COULD END UP
GOING FREE...

23:09.622 --> 23:12.056
UNLESS <i>YOU</i> SPEAK UP.

23:13.759 --> 23:15.693
IS THAT
WHAT YOU WANT TO HAPPEN?

23:15.695 --> 23:17.628
NO. NO. NO, SHARON.

23:17.630 --> 23:19.630
OBVIOUSLY,
I DON'T WANT THAT TO HAPPEN.

23:19.632 --> 23:22.166
BUT EVEN -- EVEN IF I-I PLEAD
THE FIFTH OR WHATEVER,

23:22.168 --> 23:23.801
PEOPLE WILL FIND OUT
ABOUT ME.

23:25.237 --> 23:27.104
[ SLAPS LEGS ]
THEY WILL.

23:28.507 --> 23:30.841
[ Voice breaking ]
AND THEY WILL ALSO FIND OUT...

23:32.778 --> 23:37.782
...THAT UNDER...
VERY DIFFICULT CIRCUMSTANCES

23:37.784 --> 23:39.617
AND AGAINST
YOUR OWN BEST INTERESTS

23:39.619 --> 23:41.619
THAT RUSTY BECK
WAS THE KIND OF PERSON

23:41.621 --> 23:43.988
WHO WAS BRAVE ENOUGH
TO DO THE RIGHT THING.

23:46.024 --> 23:51.762
AND WHATEVER I CAN DO
TO HELP YOU TALK WITH EMMA,

23:51.764 --> 23:53.831
I PROMISE YOU
I WILL DO.

23:56.535 --> 23:58.135
ALL RIGHT?

24:02.073 --> 24:04.074
Emma: I ASSUME
PROGRESS HAS BEEN MADE?

24:04.076 --> 24:06.076
LIEUTENANTS FLYNN AND PROVENZA
ARE OUT

24:06.078 --> 24:09.013
PICKING UP MARTIN ELLIOT'S
FAKE-ALIBI WITNESS.

24:09.015 --> 24:10.681
JENNIFER O'BRIEN.

24:10.683 --> 24:12.283
SHE'S ACTING IN A MOVIE
HE'S FILMING RIGHT NOW.

24:12.285 --> 24:14.585
HONESTLY,
I'VE BEEN THINKING ABOUT IT,

24:14.587 --> 24:16.921
AND THE TAPE OF ELLIOT
ASKING SOMEONE TO LIE FOR HIM

24:16.923 --> 24:18.956
IS ALL I NEED
TO GO TO TRIAL ON MURDER ONE.

24:18.958 --> 24:20.024
TRIAL?

24:20.026 --> 24:22.960
WHO WANTS TO GO TO TRIAL?
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

24:22.962 --> 24:27.231
I WANT TO PUT THE KILLER
IN JAIL FOR LIFE <i>TODAY.</i>

24:27.233 --> 24:28.299
OKAY, HOLD ON --

24:28.301 --> 24:30.034
YOU WANT A DEAL.
I KNOW.

24:30.036 --> 24:33.237
BUT YOU HAVE NO WITNESSES,
NOTHING UNDER HIS FINGERNAILS,

24:33.239 --> 24:35.005
HUGE TIME-OF-DEATH ISSUES,

24:35.007 --> 24:37.041
AND JURIES LOVE PATTERNS --

24:37.043 --> 24:40.578
TWO WIVES, TWO DRUG DEATHS,
MAYBE TWO KNIVES,

24:40.580 --> 24:42.112
A MISTRESS
DURING EVERY MARRIAGE.

24:42.114 --> 24:44.014
I CAN WIN THIS.
REALLY?

24:44.016 --> 24:46.984
AND WHAT IF JENNIFER IS,
AS YOU SUGGEST, HIS MISTRESS?

24:46.986 --> 24:49.587
THE DEFENSE WILL SAY
THAT <i>SHE</i> KILLED THE WIFE

24:49.589 --> 24:52.189
IN ORDER TO GET
HER BOYFRIEND'S MONEY
AND HIS FANCY HOUSE.

24:52.191 --> 24:53.390
HAVE YOU THOUGHT
ABOUT THAT?

24:57.762 --> 24:59.663
AM I THE ONLY PERSON HERE
WHO UNDERSTANDS

24:59.665 --> 25:01.599
THAT WE CAN'T HOLD MR. ELLIOT
MUCH LONGER

25:01.601 --> 25:02.900
WITHOUT ARRESTING HIM?

25:02.902 --> 25:05.269
AND IF WE LET HIM GO
AND HE KILLS SOMEONE ELSE,

25:05.271 --> 25:07.304
WE'LL BE FACING
HUGE LIABILITY ISSUES.

25:07.306 --> 25:08.606
MM.

25:08.608 --> 25:09.874
I'VE NEVER HAD
A DETECTIVE

25:09.876 --> 25:11.675
TRY AND TALK ME OUT OF
FILING CHARGES BEFORE.

25:11.677 --> 25:15.613
THAT'S BECAUSE YOU'RE NEW
TO THE BIG-PROFILE HOMICIDES.

25:15.615 --> 25:20.017
YOU SEE, WE DON'T JUST
ARREST PEOPLE ANYMORE, EMMA.

25:20.019 --> 25:22.119
WE HELP
GET THEM CONVICTED.

25:22.121 --> 25:24.922
NOW, DO YOU WANT
TO ALTER THAT DYNAMIC?

25:24.924 --> 25:26.657
SHOULD I CALL THE D.A.

25:26.659 --> 25:29.927
AND ASK IF YOU REPRESENT
A CHANGE IN POLICY?

25:32.063 --> 25:34.198
IF I MAY, SOME ADVICE.

25:34.200 --> 25:36.634
TOO MUCH PRESSURE
CAN BACKFIRE

25:36.636 --> 25:38.903
IN A MURDER INVESTIGATION
LIKE THIS.

25:38.905 --> 25:41.939
IS THAT A KNOCK ON ME
WANTING TO INTERVIEW
YOUR FOSTER SON TODAY?

25:45.677 --> 25:48.913
ONE OF THE NICE THINGS
ABOUT ME, D.D.A. RIOS,

25:48.915 --> 25:52.216
IS THAT WHEN I'M REALLY UNHAPPY
ABOUT SOMETHING,

25:52.218 --> 25:54.251
PEOPLE NEVER HAVE TO ASK.

25:55.921 --> 25:56.921
[ CHUCKLES SOFTLY ]

25:56.923 --> 25:58.188
FINE.

25:58.190 --> 26:00.925
FOR NOW, MARTIN ELLIOT
IS <i>YOUR</i> PROBLEM,

26:00.927 --> 26:02.726
AND RUSTY BECK IS MINE.

26:02.728 --> 26:05.729
I EXPECT TO FINISH
MY CONVERSATION WITH HIM <i>TODAY,</i>

26:05.731 --> 26:06.797
AS PROMISED.

26:10.101 --> 26:12.136
Taylor: OKAY.

26:12.138 --> 26:13.837
SO...
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

26:13.839 --> 26:17.074
WHAT IF THIS JENNIFER O'BRIEN,
MARTIN'S FAKE-ALIBI WITNESS,

26:17.076 --> 26:18.342
DOESN'T COOPERATE
WITH YOU?

26:18.344 --> 26:20.811
UNCOOPERATIVE WITNESSES
ARE BECOMING

26:20.813 --> 26:22.313
A SPECIALTY OF MINE.

26:22.315 --> 26:24.415
WE JUST NEED TO GET JENNIFER
IN THE RIGHT FRAME OF MIND

26:24.417 --> 26:26.083
AND ASK HER
THE PROPER QUESTIONS.

26:26.085 --> 26:29.687
WHAT KIND OF QUESTIONS?

26:29.689 --> 26:31.288
Provenza:
WHY ARE WE PARKING <i>HERE?</i>

26:31.290 --> 26:33.023
GEEZ.

26:33.025 --> 26:35.159
THE WOMAN LIVES
A BLOCK AWAY.

26:35.161 --> 26:37.828
AND WHY ARE YOU WALKING
LIKE A CLOWN?

26:37.830 --> 26:41.098
GOT A PHYSICAL IN A MONTH.
I'M DOING 10,000 STEPS A DAY.

26:41.100 --> 26:43.133
IT LOWERS MY PULSE.

26:43.135 --> 26:45.102
YOU SHOULD TRY IT.

26:45.104 --> 26:48.238
I DIDN'T GET A TROPHY
FOR OUTLASTING MY ENTIRE CLASS

26:48.240 --> 26:50.007
BY COUNTING MY STEPS.

26:50.009 --> 26:52.009
OH, YEAH?
SO, WHAT'S YOUR SECRET, THEN?

26:52.011 --> 26:53.978
MY DOCTOR HAS A PROBLEM
WITH MY HEALTH,

26:53.980 --> 26:55.913
I GET MY X-RAYS
TOUCHED UP.

26:55.915 --> 26:58.983
AND I STOPPED DRINKING ALCOHOL
AND SWITCHED TO WHITE WINE.

26:58.985 --> 27:01.118
YOU KNOW...

27:01.120 --> 27:04.888
I DON'T REALLY KNOW
WHY I'M WORKING AT ALL.

27:04.890 --> 27:08.492
I'M NOT <i>COUNTING</i> MY STEPS.
I'M <i>RETRACING</i> THEM.

27:08.494 --> 27:11.328
I SHOULD JUST RETIRE --
PLAY GOLF.

27:11.330 --> 27:13.130
[ CHUCKLES ]
"PLAY GOLF."

27:13.132 --> 27:14.865
AND WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO
THE WEEK AFTER <i>THAT?</i>

27:14.867 --> 27:18.335
3,008, 9, 10, 11, 12...

27:21.272 --> 27:23.007
GOOD MORNING.

27:23.009 --> 27:25.209
LIEUTENANT FLYNN,
LIEUTENANT PROVENZA, L.A.P.D.

27:25.211 --> 27:27.411
WE WOULD LIKE YOU
TO COME DOWNTOWN WITH US

27:27.413 --> 27:30.047
FOR AN HOUR OR SO
TO DISCUSS MARTIN ELLIOT.

27:30.049 --> 27:31.215
OH.

27:31.217 --> 27:32.883
WELL, UM...

27:32.885 --> 27:34.818
I HEARD WHAT HAPPENED
TO HIS WIFE.

27:34.820 --> 27:37.488
BUT, YOU KNOW, I DON'T
REALLY KNOW MARTIN OUTSIDE WORK.

27:37.490 --> 27:39.156
HMM. ME EITHER.

27:39.158 --> 27:40.324
Man: WHO IS IT, BABE?

27:40.326 --> 27:42.926
UH...UH,
THIS IS MY HUSBAND, DANNY.

27:42.928 --> 27:45.896
UM, IT'S THE POLICE --
ABOUT MARTIN.

27:45.898 --> 27:48.198
JUST --
UH, ONE SECOND, OFFICERS.

27:53.471 --> 27:55.039
[ CHUCKLES ]

27:55.041 --> 27:56.340
HUSBAND.

27:57.909 --> 27:59.510
DANNY'S AN ACTOR, TOO.

27:59.512 --> 28:02.046
IT'S HARD FOR HIM
WHEN I'M WORKING AND HE'S NOT.

28:02.048 --> 28:04.048
PLUS, DEALING
WITH ALL THE EXTRA STUFF

28:04.050 --> 28:06.283
THAT MARTIN
WANTS ME TO DO.

28:06.285 --> 28:07.785
LIKE...
WHAT EXTRA STUFF?

28:07.787 --> 28:10.087
WELL,
MARTIN LOVES REHEARSING.

28:10.089 --> 28:11.455
I BET.

28:11.457 --> 28:13.090
AND WHERE DO YOU <i>DO</i> THAT?

28:13.092 --> 28:16.493
UH, THE STAGE, THE PARKING LOT,
THE LOCATION.

28:16.495 --> 28:19.296
NIGHT BEFORE LAST,
WE WERE WORKING IN HIS TRAILER

28:19.298 --> 28:22.066
FROM LIKE 7:00 TO 10:00 --
SOMETHING LIKE THAT.

28:29.841 --> 28:32.209
I THOUGHT YOU SAID
WE WERE GOING DOWNTOWN.

28:32.211 --> 28:34.812
WHY -- WHY ARE WE
AT MARTIN'S HOUSE?

28:34.814 --> 28:36.213
[ ENGINE SHUTS OFF ]

28:36.215 --> 28:38.082
WELL.

28:38.084 --> 28:40.884
I THOUGHT YOU WEREN'T FRIENDS
WITH MARTIN OUTSIDE OF WORK.

28:40.886 --> 28:42.286
YET SHE KNOWS
WHERE HE LIVES.

28:42.288 --> 28:44.021
GUESS YOU MUST HAVE BEEN HERE
BEFORE, HUH?

28:44.023 --> 28:45.856
DID YOU EVER MEET HIS WIFE,
GRETCHEN?

28:45.858 --> 28:47.257
DIRTY BLOND,
ABOUT YOUR HEIGHT,

28:47.259 --> 28:49.827
STABBED SEVERAL TIMES
IN THE CHEST AND STOMACH?

28:49.829 --> 28:51.962
MAYBE SHE KNOWS
THE ALARM CODES TO THE HOUSE.

28:51.964 --> 28:53.030
OHH.

28:53.032 --> 28:54.531
YOU EVER GO SWIMMING
IN THE POOL?

28:54.533 --> 28:57.234
OR GO IN THE KITCHEN
AND SEE ALL THE SHARP KNIVES?

28:57.236 --> 28:59.536
WHAT ARE YOU
ACCUSING ME OF?

28:59.538 --> 29:02.506
LISTEN, SWEETIE, I'M NOT SAYING
<i>THAT THIS IS GONNA HAPPEN,</i>

29:02.508 --> 29:05.075
<i>BUT IF THE POLICE CALL YOU,</i>
<i>I NEED YOU TO TELL THEM</i>

29:05.077 --> 29:07.544
<i>THAT I WAS WITH YOU</i>
<i>LAST NIGHT.</i>

29:07.546 --> 29:10.380
YOU DON'T KNOW MARTIN ELLIOT
THAT WELL,

29:10.382 --> 29:13.851
SO YOU THOUGHT, "WHY NOT
COMMIT A FELONY FOR HIM?"

29:13.853 --> 29:16.887
[ Voice breaking ]
LOOK, MARTIN CONSTANTLY
THREATENS TO FIRE ME, ALL RIGHT?

29:16.889 --> 29:18.455
<i>HE -- HE CALLS ME</i>
<i>A TERRIBLE ACTRESS.</i>

29:18.457 --> 29:20.390
<i>SO I-I LET HIM THINK</i>
<i>THAT HE OWNS ME,</i>

29:20.392 --> 29:23.260
BUT IT'S JUST SO I END UP
IN THE FINAL CUT OF HIS FILM.

29:23.262 --> 29:24.895
<i>WHAT DO YOU WANT</i>
<i>FROM ME?</i>

29:24.897 --> 29:27.297
WE WANT TO KNOW
WHERE MARTIN WAS THAT NIGHT.

29:28.600 --> 29:31.001
MAYBE HER HUSBAND
COULD TELL US.

29:31.003 --> 29:32.436
AH.

29:32.438 --> 29:33.570
SHE HAS A HUSBAND?

29:33.572 --> 29:35.038
Jennifer: <i>OKAY, UH...</i>

29:35.040 --> 29:37.341
WHO MAY HAVE FOUND OUT
ABOUT THE AFFAIR

29:37.343 --> 29:39.376
AND TRIED TO FRAME
OUR SUSPECT.

29:39.378 --> 29:41.879
THIS IS GONNA MAKE
MARTIN LOOK REALLY BAD,
BUT HE STOOD ME UP.

29:41.881 --> 29:44.281
I WAITED FOR HIM
FROM 7:00 ON,

29:44.283 --> 29:46.550
BUT I DON'T KNOW WHAT HAPPENED
TO HIM OR WHAT HE WAS DOING.

29:46.552 --> 29:48.285
ALL RIGHT. WHERE WERE YOU
WAITING FOR HIM?

29:48.287 --> 29:50.220
THE HOTEL PERINO,
BUNGALOW 9.

29:51.422 --> 29:52.890
WAIT A MINUTE.

29:52.892 --> 29:54.558
DIDN'T GRETCHEN ELLIOT
RECEIVE A CALL

29:54.560 --> 29:56.960
FROM THE HOTEL PERINO
THE NIGHT SHE DIED?

29:56.962 --> 29:58.128
YES, SHE DID.

29:58.130 --> 29:59.897
BUT IF JENNIFER WAS
AT THE HOTEL,

29:59.899 --> 30:01.431
WHY WOULD SHE CALL
GRETCHEN?

30:01.433 --> 30:03.100
WELL, BECAUSE IF YOU'RE GONNA
DROP BY AND KILL SOMEBODY,

30:03.102 --> 30:05.068
IT'S A GOOD IDEA
TO MAKE SURE THEY'RE HOME.

30:05.070 --> 30:06.904
OKAY.

30:06.906 --> 30:08.906
I WAS MAYBE PUSHING TO FILE
TOO SOON.

30:08.908 --> 30:10.574
BUT REMEMBER THIS --

30:10.576 --> 30:14.411
I'LL BE THE ONE WHO <i>ULTIMATELY</i>
<i>DECIDES WHETHER WE DEAL.</i>

30:14.413 --> 30:16.680
AND I LOOK FORWARD
TO CLEARING UP

30:16.682 --> 30:18.448
ALL THIS CONFUSION
WITH RUSTY.

30:18.450 --> 30:20.617
Flynn:
<i>HOTEL PERINO, BUNGALOW 9.</i>

30:20.619 --> 30:22.386
<i>DID YOU SAVE YOUR ROOM KEY?</i>

30:22.388 --> 30:24.188
NO, I-I DON'T THINK SO.

30:24.190 --> 30:26.323
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

30:37.235 --> 30:39.236
IT'S NICE TO SEE
WHERE THE OTHER HALF CHEATS.

30:39.238 --> 30:40.571
[ CHUCKLES ]

30:40.573 --> 30:43.140
WELCOME TO THE HOTEL PERINO.
HOW MAY I HELP YOU?

30:43.142 --> 30:44.241
WE'RE FROM THE L.A.P.D.

30:44.243 --> 30:46.610
THIS PLACE IS AMAZING.

30:46.612 --> 30:48.378
HOW MUCH ARE YOUR ROOMS?

30:48.380 --> 30:50.514
OUR SUPERIOR SUITE
STARTS AT $1,300 A NIGHT.

30:50.516 --> 30:52.649
WE WANT TO LOOK
AT BUNGALOW 9.

30:52.651 --> 30:54.685
I'M SORRY.
IT'S NOT AVAILABLE RIGHT NOW.

30:54.687 --> 30:56.220
[ FAX MACHINE BEEPS ]
I APOLOGIZE.

30:56.222 --> 30:57.554
UH, HOLD ON.

30:57.556 --> 30:59.489
BUZZ, SEE WHAT THAT FAX IS
COMING IN BACK THERE.

30:59.491 --> 31:01.158
UM,
I-I-I BEG YOUR PARDON.

31:01.160 --> 31:03.193
EMPLOYEES ARE THE ONLY ONES
ALLOWED TO -- TO --

31:03.195 --> 31:05.028
WAIT -- WHAT --
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?!

31:05.030 --> 31:06.430
IT'S OUR SEARCH WARRANT,
LIEUTENANT.

31:06.432 --> 31:09.032
BUZZ, DOES THAT THING
FAX <i>AND</i> PRINT?

31:09.034 --> 31:10.267
UH, YES, SIR.
SCANS, TOO.

31:10.269 --> 31:12.002
OOH.

31:12.004 --> 31:13.437
WE NEED THE KEY TO BUNGALOW 9
AND FOR YOU TO TELL US

31:13.439 --> 31:15.105
WHO HAD IT BOOKED
THE NIGHT BEFORE LAST.

31:15.107 --> 31:16.640
IF YOU'D JUST LET ME
TALK TO MY MANAGER --

31:16.642 --> 31:18.242
LISTEN TO ME.

31:18.244 --> 31:21.144
YOU DELAY US ONE MORE TIME,
AND I'M GONNA ARREST YOU

31:21.146 --> 31:23.113
FOR INTERFERING
WITH A POLICE INVESTIGATION.

31:23.115 --> 31:24.514
YOU UNDERSTAND?

31:24.516 --> 31:27.985
BUNGALOW 9 HAS A RESERVATION
EVERY WEDNESDAY

31:27.987 --> 31:30.187
ON A CORPORATE ACCOUNT --
RIVERWAY FILMS.

31:30.189 --> 31:31.388
MARTIN ELLIOT'S COMPANY.
MM-HMM.

31:31.390 --> 31:32.456
EXCUSE ME.

31:32.458 --> 31:36.560
WHAT KIND OF RECORDING LOOP
IS THAT SURVEILLANCE CAMERA ON?

31:36.562 --> 31:39.096
ONE DAY? ONE WEEK?

31:39.098 --> 31:41.531
UH...SECURITY'S
ALL IN THE BACK OFFICE.

31:41.533 --> 31:43.667
Flynn: HMM.
AND THAT ROOM IS WHERE?

31:43.669 --> 31:46.036
I CAN TAKE YOU,
IF YOU LIKE.

31:46.038 --> 31:48.472
SO, THIS IS A FEW SECONDS
BEFORE THE TIMECODE MATCH

31:48.474 --> 31:50.274
FOR THE PHONE CALL
FROM THE PERINO

31:50.276 --> 31:51.608
TO GRETCHEN'S CELL.

31:51.610 --> 31:53.010
Flynn: HEY, ENLARGE
THE UPPER-LEFT CORNER THERE.

31:53.012 --> 31:54.678
LOOK WHO'S USING
THE HOUSE PHONE.

31:54.680 --> 31:57.047
Provenza: THE GIRLFRIEND SAID
SHE WAS HERE,

31:57.049 --> 31:58.682
SO THAT'S
NO BIG SURPRISE.

31:58.684 --> 32:01.285
YEAH, BUT WHY CALL
FROM THE LOBBY

32:01.287 --> 32:02.753
WHEN YOU'RE
IN BUNGALOW 9?

32:04.589 --> 32:06.223
WHAT WAY IS SHE GOING?

32:06.225 --> 32:08.558
TOWARD
THE PARKING-GARAGE ELEVATOR.

32:10.628 --> 32:14.097
PARKING-GARAGE ANGLE'S
OVER HERE.

32:22.573 --> 32:23.573
WAIT A MINUTE.

32:23.575 --> 32:26.043
REWIND THAT.

32:26.045 --> 32:28.111
[ KEYBOARD CLACKING ]

32:30.615 --> 32:32.249
YEAH. FREEZE IT.

32:32.251 --> 32:34.051
NOW BLOW IT UP.

32:34.053 --> 32:36.453
THAT'S NOT
THE GIRLFRIEND.

32:36.455 --> 32:38.388
THAT'S HIS EX-WIFE.

32:47.432 --> 32:48.732
SO,
YOU WENT TO THE HOTEL

32:48.734 --> 32:50.534
TO MAKE SURE
JENNIFER HAD ARRIVED,

32:50.536 --> 32:52.235
WHICH MEANT
MARTIN WAS COMING.

32:52.237 --> 32:54.838
CALLED THE HOUSE AND CONFIRMED
GRETCHEN WAS IN THE HOME

32:54.840 --> 32:56.273
THAT USED TO BE YOURS.

32:57.408 --> 33:00.243
YOU CAN'T EVEN PLACE MY CLIENT
AT THE CRIME SCENE.

33:00.245 --> 33:02.112
WE JUST LEARNED
FROM OUR MEDICAL EXAMINER

33:02.114 --> 33:04.548
THAT VALIUM WAS PRESENT
IN GRETCHEN ELLIOT'S BODY.

33:04.550 --> 33:07.551
SO WHAT?
VALIUM'S A VERY COMMON DRUG.

33:07.553 --> 33:09.086
SO COMMON, IN FACT,

33:09.088 --> 33:10.854
THAT MR. ELLIOT'S FIRST WIFE,
BRITTANY,

33:10.856 --> 33:13.623
ALSO HAD VALIUM IN <i>HER</i> BODY
THE NIGHT THAT <i>SHE</i> DIED.

33:13.625 --> 33:16.193
Emma: WHAT SHE <i>DIDN'T</i> HAVE
WAS A PRESCRIPTION.

33:16.195 --> 33:17.527
NEITHER DID GRETCHEN.

33:17.529 --> 33:19.296
BRITTANY
COMMITTED SUICIDE.

33:19.298 --> 33:20.764
WE'RE RETHINKING THAT,
ASHLEY.

33:20.766 --> 33:23.667
<i>WE'RE RETHINKING THAT</i>
<i>VERY HARD.</i>

33:23.669 --> 33:26.103
<i>RIGHT NOW,</i>
<i>I HAVE MY DETECTIVES</i>

33:26.105 --> 33:27.637
<i>SEARCHING YOUR HOUSE</i>
<i>FOR VALIUM.</i>

33:27.639 --> 33:30.507
<i>AND ALSO, AS YOU KNOW,</i>
<i>WHEN YOU STAB A PERSON</i>

33:30.509 --> 33:31.808
AS MANY TIMES AS YOU DID,

33:31.810 --> 33:33.610
THERE'S LOTS AND LOTS OF BLOOD
TO CLEAN UP.

33:33.612 --> 33:34.845
YOU CAN'T
GET RID OF IT ALL.

33:34.847 --> 33:37.114
EVEN WHEN YOU GO HOME

33:37.116 --> 33:41.184
AND YOU WASH, WASH, WASH
YOUR CAR,

33:41.186 --> 33:42.252
YOU MISS IT.

33:42.254 --> 33:44.254
Emma: SO, THOSE DETECTIVES

33:44.256 --> 33:46.757
ARE ALSO LOOKING FOR BLOOD
IN YOUR VEHICLE.

33:46.759 --> 33:48.392
AND THEY'RE GONNA FIND IT.

33:48.394 --> 33:51.661
ONE DROP OF BLOOD,
ONE DOSE OF VALIUM,

33:51.663 --> 33:53.630
THEY CALL THIS PHONE.

33:56.134 --> 33:59.269
THE OFFER IS TWO
SECOND-DEGREE-MURDER CHARGES --

33:59.271 --> 34:01.738
30 YEARS, CONSECUTIVE.

34:01.740 --> 34:04.608
AND IT'S ONLY GOOD UNTIL
THAT CELLPHONE STARTS RINGING.

34:32.303 --> 34:34.204
HEY.
HEY.

34:34.206 --> 34:36.306
UH, DON'T TELL SHARON
I TALKED TO YOU, OKAY?

34:36.308 --> 34:38.875
MY SHORT-TERM MEMORY
WILL TAKE CARE OF THAT.

34:38.877 --> 34:41.311
WHAT'S ON YOUR MIND?

34:41.313 --> 34:44.915
I'VE DECIDED TO...ANSWER
ALL THOSE STUPID QUESTIONS

34:44.917 --> 34:46.683
EMMA'S ASKING ME --
ON TWO CONDITIONS --

34:46.685 --> 34:48.351
EVEN THOUGH IT MEANS

34:48.353 --> 34:50.220
THAT EVERYONE IN MY CLASS
WILL HATE ME FOREVER.

34:50.222 --> 34:52.422
[ Chuckling ]
WELL, YEAH.

34:52.424 --> 34:54.658
I'VE GOT A TROPHY SITTING
RIGHT OVER THERE THAT PROVES

34:54.660 --> 34:57.027
EVERYONE IN YOUR CLASS
WON'T BE <i>AROUND</i> FOREVER.

34:58.596 --> 35:00.397
WHAT ARE
YOUR TWO CONDITIONS?

35:00.399 --> 35:04.935
WELL, I'LL, UH,
I'LL TALK ABOUT THE, UM...

35:06.537 --> 35:09.773
...THE -- THE --
THE GRIFFITH PARK STUFF

35:09.775 --> 35:11.408
IF, UM...

35:11.410 --> 35:12.409
IF...?

35:12.411 --> 35:14.010
IF SHARON ISN'T THERE.

35:15.913 --> 35:20.617
LOOK, I-I CAN'T GO OVER IT AGAIN
IN FRONT OF HER,

35:20.619 --> 35:23.687
AND -- AND I DON'T WANT HER
TO KNOW

35:23.689 --> 35:25.555
THAT I ASKED HER
NOT TO BE THERE.

35:27.225 --> 35:29.259
I SEE.

35:29.261 --> 35:30.627
OKAY.

35:30.629 --> 35:33.296
I'LL HANDLE THAT.

35:33.298 --> 35:34.798
WHAT'S
YOUR OTHER CONDITION?

35:34.800 --> 35:36.967
WELL, I DON'T WANT <i>YOU</i> THERE,
EITHER.

35:37.969 --> 35:39.503
WHY?

35:39.505 --> 35:41.404
LOOK, IF -- IF YOU HEAR
THE WHOLE STORY,

35:41.406 --> 35:42.706
YOU WON'T LIKE ME
ANYMORE.

35:42.708 --> 35:44.374
OH --

35:44.376 --> 35:45.909
I-I KNOW -- I KNOW YOU THINK
YOU WILL, BUT YOU WON'T.

35:45.911 --> 35:48.912
THERE'S STUFF THAT I DID
THAT -- THAT...

35:50.815 --> 35:53.517
LOOK, I-I JUST --
I NEED YOU, LIEUTENANT.

35:53.519 --> 35:54.784
I NEED YOU
TO BE MY FRIEND.

35:54.786 --> 35:56.553
OKAY?

35:56.555 --> 36:00.290
SO JUST -- JUST LET ME
TALK TO EMMA BY MYSELF.

36:00.292 --> 36:01.358
PLEASE.

36:03.694 --> 36:05.629
OKAY.

36:05.631 --> 36:08.632
AND, UH, CAN YOU...
MAKE SHARON THINK

36:08.634 --> 36:10.400
THAT IT WAS, LIKE,
ALL    <i>YO</i>IDEA?

36:10.402 --> 36:12.536
[ Chuckling ] WELL...

36:12.538 --> 36:15.906
I HAVE NO PROBLEM TAKING CREDIT
FOR OTHER PEOPLE'S IDEAS.

36:15.908 --> 36:18.608
HOW DO YOU THINK
I BECAME A LIEUTENANT?

36:20.645 --> 36:22.946
THE LAST OF MY KIND.

36:31.889 --> 36:34.024
[ SIGHS ]

36:35.059 --> 36:36.693
[ DOOR OPENS ]

36:38.396 --> 36:40.697
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

36:40.699 --> 36:43.066
SO, HAS THE SUSPECT
GIVEN US HER ANSWER YET?

36:45.436 --> 36:46.937
PLAN "B."

36:49.607 --> 36:51.708
[ DIALING ]

36:53.811 --> 36:55.879
[ CELLPHONE VIBRATING ]

36:57.982 --> 36:59.015
OH.

36:59.017 --> 37:00.350
GOSH.

37:00.352 --> 37:03.453
I WONDER WHO THAT IS.

37:06.857 --> 37:09.092
[ VIBRATING CONTINUES ]

37:09.094 --> 37:10.727
FOR THE RECORD,

37:10.729 --> 37:14.397
<i>EVERYTHING MY CLIENT SAYS</i>
<i>IS HYPOTHETICAL</i>

37:14.399 --> 37:16.466
<i>UNTIL WE AGREE</i>
<i>ON SENTENCING.</i>

37:16.468 --> 37:18.535
[ VIBRATING STOPS ]

37:24.475 --> 37:28.345
BOY, THIS DID NOT WORK OUT
THE WAY I HOPED AT ALL.

37:28.347 --> 37:29.879
REALLY?

37:29.881 --> 37:31.615
WHAT DID YOU HOPE FOR?

37:31.617 --> 37:35.485
MARTIN IN PRISON --
UNABLE TO REPRODUCE.

37:36.654 --> 37:38.722
I STILL GET HIS SCHEDULE,
YOU KNOW,

37:38.724 --> 37:41.358
SO WHEN IT POPPED UP
AGAIN ON HIS CALENDAR,
I KNEW WHAT IT MEANT.

37:41.360 --> 37:42.559
WHAT POPPED UP?

37:42.561 --> 37:43.793
"WEDNESDAY NIGHTS

37:43.795 --> 37:46.129
7:00 TO 10:00 --
WATCHING DAILIES."

37:46.131 --> 37:47.764
<i>AND THAT'S A PROBLEM</i>
<i>BECAUSE...?</i>

37:47.766 --> 37:49.499
BECAUSE THAT'S WHAT HE PUT
<i>ON HIS SCHEDULE</i>

37:49.501 --> 37:50.834
WHEN <i>WE</i> FIRST
GOT TOGETHER.

37:50.836 --> 37:53.436
IT MEANT HE WAS CHEATING
[Laughing] ON GRETCHEN.

37:54.772 --> 37:57.407
WHEN SHE TOLD ME
SHE WAS PREGNANT LAST MONTH,

37:57.409 --> 37:58.642
I ALREADY KNEW.

37:58.644 --> 38:00.410
WHY DID YOU CARE
ABOUT THAT?

38:00.412 --> 38:05.048
BECAUSE MARTIN PROMISED ME --
NO MORE KIDS.

38:05.050 --> 38:08.051
AND WHEN I CONFRONTED HIM
ABOUT GRETCHEN GETTING PREGNANT,

38:08.053 --> 38:09.552
HE BLEW ME OFF BY SAYING

38:09.554 --> 38:11.655
HE WANTED A SECOND CHANCE
TO BE A FATHER.

38:11.657 --> 38:13.423
MARTIN CAN REPLACE ME.
I DON'T CARE.

38:13.425 --> 38:14.924
BUT HE CAN'T REPLACE
MY BOYS.

38:14.926 --> 38:17.961
SO, SINCE HE NEVER CHANGES,
I KNEW WHEN AND WHERE TO BE --

38:17.963 --> 38:21.564
EARLY WEDNESDAY NIGHT
AT THE PERINO, BUNGALOW 9 --

38:21.566 --> 38:23.733
THE SAME PLACE <i>WE</i> WENT.

38:25.136 --> 38:26.670
I WAITED IN THE LOBBY

38:26.672 --> 38:28.838
TO MAKE SURE THE NEXT
MRS. ELLIOT WAS COMING IN,

38:28.840 --> 38:31.074
AND THEN
I PAID GRETCHEN A VISIT,

38:31.076 --> 38:35.045
PUT VALIUM IN THE ORGANIC
SMOOTHIE I BROUGHT HER,

38:35.047 --> 38:36.780
CALMED SOME NERVES
WHEN SHE GOT DIZZY,

38:36.782 --> 38:38.915
AND THEN I TOOK A KNIFE
FROM THE SET IN THE KITCHEN

38:38.917 --> 38:41.051
THAT WAS PART OF A WEDDING
PRESENT TO MARTIN AND ME

38:41.053 --> 38:44.120
THAT HE FOUGHT FOR
IN THE DIVORCE, AND...

38:46.023 --> 38:47.123
YOU HAVE TO SAY IT.

38:53.431 --> 38:54.898
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

38:54.900 --> 38:58.568
I STABBED GRETCHEN TO DEATH
AND DUMPED HER IN THE POOL.

39:00.004 --> 39:03.707
ASHLEY, WHAT ABOUT MR. ELLIOT'S
<i>FIRST WIFE, BRITTANY?</i>

39:03.709 --> 39:05.008
WHAT ABOUT THAT?

39:05.010 --> 39:06.609
THE DEAL
IS FOR <i>TWO</i> SECOND-DEGREES.

39:08.813 --> 39:12.248
WHAT HAPPENED
TO BRITTANY...

39:13.751 --> 39:15.585
[ CHUCKLES ]

39:15.587 --> 39:18.288
I GUESS YOU'LL JUST HAVE TO
WONDER ABOUT THAT.

39:19.757 --> 39:23.159
WHICH IS MORE
THAN MARTIN EVER DID.

39:40.911 --> 39:42.112
YOU WANT ME TO PUT THIS
WHERE THE OLD ONE WAS?TER.

39:42.114 --> 39:43.747
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.
RIGHT HERE.

39:43.749 --> 39:45.849
IT GOES RIGHT HERE.

39:45.851 --> 39:48.051
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,

39:48.053 --> 39:53.623
I HAVE PURCHASED
THIS PRINTER/COPIER/FAX/SCANNER

39:53.625 --> 39:55.759
AS MY GIFT
TO ALL OF YOU --

39:55.761 --> 39:59.696
YOUR OWN LITTLE PART
OF MY CASH PRIZE.

39:59.698 --> 40:01.030
A GIFT? WOW.

40:01.032 --> 40:03.666
THAT'S SO...UNLIKE YOU.

40:03.668 --> 40:09.172
WELL, THE WIRELESS PASSWORD
WILL COST EACH OF YOU 20 BUCKS.

40:09.174 --> 40:12.175
BUT WITH THAT, YOU GET
THE LOW, LOW FAMILY DISCOUNT

40:12.177 --> 40:14.778
OF 5 CENTS PER PAGE.

40:14.780 --> 40:15.912
[ CHUCKLES ]

40:19.817 --> 40:21.518
WAIT A SECOND.

40:21.520 --> 40:23.186
WHAT ARE MY BOYS
DOING HERE?

40:23.188 --> 40:25.054
YOU'RE THEIR FATHER.

40:25.056 --> 40:26.656
Emma: CONGRATULATIONS.

40:26.658 --> 40:29.058
YOU JUST WON SOLE CUSTODY
OF YOUR CHILDREN.

40:29.060 --> 40:30.193
BUT...

40:30.195 --> 40:32.529
I'M MAKING A MOVIE
RIGHT NOW.

40:32.531 --> 40:35.165
Sharon: YOU SAID YOU WANTED
A SECOND CHANCE WITH YOUR KIDS.

40:35.167 --> 40:36.533
HERE IT IS.

40:36.535 --> 40:38.802
LISTEN,
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND.

40:38.804 --> 40:42.238
THIS IS <i>THE</i> MOST IMPORTANT FILM
OF MY CAREER.

40:42.240 --> 40:43.673
MORE IMPORTANT
THAN YOUR SONS?

40:43.675 --> 40:45.308
ANYBODY CAN BABYSIT!

40:45.310 --> 40:48.111
<i>I'M</i> THE ONLY ONE
WHO CAN DIRECT THIS MOVIE!

40:48.113 --> 40:49.813
DAMN IT!

40:49.815 --> 40:54.317
WHY ARE YOU
TRYING TO PUNISH ME?

40:54.319 --> 40:56.252
[ DOOR OPENS ]

40:56.254 --> 40:57.921
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

41:02.960 --> 41:04.961
[ DOOR OPENS ]

41:04.963 --> 41:07.330
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

41:11.235 --> 41:14.237
WHO WILL THOSE BOYS HAVE
TO STICK UP FOR THEM NOW?

41:16.073 --> 41:19.275
Sharon: AS LIEUTENANT PROVENZA
REMINDED ME,

41:19.277 --> 41:22.312
SOONER OR LATER, ALL KIDS
HAVE TO STICK UP FOR THEMSELVES,

41:22.314 --> 41:25.715
AND WE DON'T GET TO CHOOSE
WHEN THEY'RE READY FOR THAT.

41:27.117 --> 41:30.119
YOUR MATERIAL WITNESS
IS OUT OF SUMMER SCHOOL.

41:30.121 --> 41:32.121
AS AGREED,
YOU WILL NOT CALL HIM NAMES.

41:32.123 --> 41:36.759
YOU WILL ADHERE STRICTLY
TO THE FACTS OF YOUR CASE.

41:38.929 --> 41:42.265
HE STILL SHOULDN'T BE
LIVING WITH YOU.

41:42.267 --> 41:43.666
GET OVER IT.
